    "enabled": true,
    "scope": "global",
    "instructions": "Save global memories for: platform-wide patterns (growth trends, seasonal activity cycles, feature adoption rates), recurring admin questions and their answers (so you get faster over time), feedback themes (what users keep asking for), organism health baselines (what \"normal\" looks like so you can detect anomalies), and key dates (market deadlines, custody trial, EIN status, coach meetings).\n\nWhat NOT to save: Individual user private data, temporary debugging, anything that should live in project documentation rather than agent memory."
